<TEXT>
   Leroy M. Fingerson, TSI president and chief executive
officer, attributed the lower-than-expected earnings to a
shortfall in sales, resulting from reduced order bookings in
the fourth quarter.
   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, TSI
dropped $1 to close at $10.50.
