<HL>
   International Brief -- Trusthouse Forte PLC:
   Hotel, Catering Concern's
   Annual Pretax Profit Rose
</HL>
<DATE>
04/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A11
</SO>
<CO>
   U.TRS
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Trusthouse Forte PLC of Britain, a hotel and catering
concern, said its annual pretax profit rose 12%, helped by
strong growth in both of its core businesses.
   Pretax earnings of #260 million ($426 million) for the
year ended Jan. 31 compare with #232 million in the year
through Oct. 31, 1988. Trusthouse Forte changed its
accounting period last year. For the latest 15-month period,
the company had pretax profit of #291 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Profit after taxes and minority interests, or profit
attributable to shareholders, increased 18% to #203 million
from #172 million, and totaled #225 million for the 15-month
period. Per-share earnings rose 18% to 25.9 pence from 22
pence, and totaled 28.7 pence for the 15 months.
   Sales increased 21% to #2.47 billion from #2.04 billion,
and for the 15 months, totaled #2.98 billion.
   The board recommended a final dividend of 7.16 pence a
share, lifting the payout for the latest year to 9.66 pence,
up from 8.4 pence in fiscal 1988. The total dividend for the
15 months was 10.66 pence.
</TEXT>
