WSJ900419-0029
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900419-0029.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Business Brief -- McClatchy Newspapers Inc.:
   Newspaper Chain's Earnings
   Plunged 51% in 1st Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
04/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8
</SO>
<CO>
   MNI
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- McClatchy Newspapers Inc. said a
sharp drop in advertising linage in March helped drive down
first-quarter earnings by 51% to $2.4 million, or eight cents
a share. The newspaper chain earned $4.85 million, or 17
cents a share, the year earlier. Revenue grew 9% to $95.1
million from $87 million.
   McClatchy added that results were hurt by startup costs
associated with a newsprint mill partnership, and costs
associated with the recent acquisition of six newspapers in
South Carolina.
</LP>
<TEXT>
